In [106]:
# Assuming Product_details is already defined as a DataFrame
Product_details = Sale[['Product_ID', 'Orders']]

# Group by 'Product_ID' and calculate the sum of orders for each group
product_orders_sum = Product_details.groupby('Product_ID')['Orders'].sum()

# Sort the results in descending order based on the sum of orders
product_orders_sum = product_orders_sum.sort_values(ascending=False)

# Display the result


plt.plot(product_orders_sum )
plt.xlabel('Product_ID')
